3||3\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tlaxcala}}\n||11||0||1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Zacatecas}}\n||10||2||1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Nayarit}}\n||9||1||2\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Campeche}}\n||8||0||1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Colima}}\n||4||0||1\n|- style=\"text-align:left; padding-left:8px;\" class=\"sortbottom\"\n| style=\"width:360px;\" colspan=\"6\"| '''Source:''' \n<small>Secretar\u00eda de Salud (2020).<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gob.mx/salud/es/archivo/prensa?idiom=es&order=DESC&page=1 |title=Prensa &#124; Archivo &#124; Secretar\u00eda de Salud &#124; Gobierno |publisher=gob.mx |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref><br>\nGeological and Atmospheric Research Institute <ref name=\"iigea1\">{{cite web|url=http://iigea.com/amag/covid-19/ |title=COVID-19 Seguimiento \u2013 IIGEA |publisher=Iigea.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n</small>\n|}\n\n=== Cases per 100,000 inhabitants ===\n\n[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants.svg|thumb|right|251xpx| Map of the COVID-19 outbreak in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants as of 5 April 2020.<br/>\n{{legend|#fee5d9|<0.1 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fcbba1|\u22650.1 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fc9272|\u22650.5 per 100,000}}{{legend|#fb6a4a|\u22651.0 per 100,000}}{{legend|#de2d26|\u22651.5 per 100,000}}{{legend|#a50f15|\u22652.0 per 100,000}}{{legend|#630606|\u22653.0 per 100,000}} {{legend|#450404|\u22655.0 per 100,000}} {{legend|#310303|\u226510.0 per 100,000}}]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display: inline-table; font-size:90%; text-align:right;\"\n|+ <big> As of April 5</big>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"  style=\"text-align:left; width:140px;\"|State\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Cases\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Population{{efn|In 2015.}}\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" | Cases per 100,000 inhabitants{{efn|Calculated by dividing the number of cases by the total population of the state and multiplying the result by 100,000.}}\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 2143\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 119,530,753\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 1.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Mexico City}}\n||560||8,918,653||6.3\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Quintana Roo}}\n||86||1,501,562||5.7\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tabasco}}\n||97||2,395,272||4.0\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Baja California Sur}}\n||28||712,029||3.9\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Aguascalientes}}\n||49||1,312,544||3.7\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Yucat\u00e1n}}\n||67||2,097,175||3.2\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Sinaloa}}\n||90||2,966,321||3.0\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Coahuila}}\n||82||2,954,915||2.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Puebla}}\n||147||6,168,883||2.4\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Baja California}}\n||69||3,315,766||2.1\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Quer\u00e9taro}}\n||38||2,038,372||1.9\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Nuevo Le\u00f3n}}\n||91||5,119,504||1.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Jalisco}}\n||123||7,844,830||1.6\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | {{Flag2|San Luis Potos\u00ed}}\n||37||2,717,820||1.4\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|State of Mexico}}\n||204||16,187,608||1.3\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Hidalgo}}\n||34||2,858,359||1.2\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Sonora}}\n||28||2,850,330||1.0\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Campeche}}\n||8||899,931||0.9\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Guanajuato}}\n||53||5,853,677||0.9\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tlaxcala}}\n||11||1,272,847||0.9\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Guerrero}}\n||30||3,533,251||0.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Morelos}}\n||15||1,903,811||0.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Nayarit}}\n||9||1,181,050||0.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tamaulipas}}\n||26||3,441,698||0.8\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Durango}}\n||12||1,754,754||0.7\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Michoac\u00e1n}}\n||30||4,584,471||0.7\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Colima}}\n||4||711,235||0.6\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Oaxaca}}\n||25||3,967,889||0.6\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Zacatecas}}\n||10||1,579,209||0.6\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Chiapas}}\n||25||5,217,908||0.5\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Veracruz}}\n||40||8,112,505||0.5\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Chihuahua}}\n||15||3,556,574||0.4\n|- style=\"text-align:left; padding-left:8px;\" class=\"sortbottom\"\n| style=\"width:360px;\" colspan=\"6\"| '''Source:''' \n<small>Secretariat of Health (2020).<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/><br>\nGeological and Atmospheric Research Institute <ref name=\"iigea1\"/><br>National Institute of Statistics and Geography <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuentame.inegi.org.mx/poblacion/habitantes.aspx?tema=P |title=N\u00famero de habitantes. Cu\u00e9ntame de M\u00e9xico |publisher=Cuentame.inegi.org.mx |date=2005-04-02 |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Curve of infection ===\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=600\n|height=400\n|colors=#FF4343\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n<!-- PLease clipboard copy the \"}x=...\" and \"y1=...\" lines from the log plot of total cases when you update these charts -->\n\n<!-- Search string CASES_X -->\n|x= Feb 28, Feb 29, Mar 1, Mar 6, Mar 7, Mar 11, Mar 12, Mar 13, Mar 14, Mar 15, Mar 16, Mar 17, Mar 18, Mar 19, Mar 20, Mar 21, Mar 22, Mar 23, Mar 24, Mar 25, Mar 26, Mar 27, Mar 28, Mar 29, Mar 30, Mar 31, Apr 1, Apr 2, Apr 3, Apr 4, Apr 5\n\n<!-- Search string CASES_Y -->\n|y1= 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 11, 15, 26, 41, 53, 82, 93, 118, 164, 203, 251,