am, second COVID-19 death in Tamil Nadu|date=2020-04-04|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|others=Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/coronavirus-tamil-nadu-records-first-death-in-madurai/article31159538.ece|title=Coronavirus: Tamil Nadu records first death in Madurai|date=2020-03-25|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|others=Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite web|url=https://stopcorona.tn.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Media-Bulletin-05-04-20-COVID-19-6-PM.pdf|title=TamilNadu Media Bulletin 05.04.2020 6PM|last=|first=|date=|website=tn.gov.in|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405215542/https://stopcorona.tn.gov.in/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Media-Bulletin-05-04-20-COVID-19-6-PM.pdf|archive-date=2020-04-05|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Telangana]]|| 50\n|9||<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=691949|title=Tablighi super spreaders cause Covid-19 explosion in India|website=www.daijiworld.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Uttar Pradesh|Uttar Pradesh]]|| 139\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/lucknow-city-coronavirus-positive-in-up-162-positivecases-reported-in-the-up-34-persons-had-attended-the-tablighi-jamaat-event-in-delhi-20161603.html|title=CoronaVirus Positive in UP : \u0924\u092c\u094d\u0932\u0940\u0917\u0940 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0936\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0932 54 \u0932\u094b\u0917\u094b\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u093f\u0932\u093e \u0938\u0902\u0915\u094d\u0930\u092e\u0923, \u0906\u0902\u0915\u0921\u093c\u093e 182 \u092a\u0939\u0941\u0902\u091a\u093e|website=Dainik Jagran|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/ups-coronavirus-count-rises-to-227-with-94-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat/article31257610.ece|title=U.P.\u2019s coronavirus count rises to 227 with 94 linked to Tablighi Jamaat|date=2020-04-04|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|others=PTI|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/lucknow-city-coronavirus-death-in-up-old-aged-man-from-varanasi-coronavirus-positive-died-third-from-up-20166377.html|title=CoronaVirus death in UP : \u0909\u0924\u094d\u0924\u0930 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0915\u094b\u0930\u094b\u0928\u093e \u0935\u093e\u092f\u0930\u0938 \u0938\u0947 \u0924\u0940\u0938\u0930\u0940 \u092e\u094c\u0924, \u0905\u092c \u0924\u0915 284 \u092a\u0949\u091c\u093f\u091f\u093f\u0935|website=Dainik Jagran|language=hi|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Uttarakhand]]\n|6\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":4\" />\n|}\n\n==== March ====\n\n* On March 18, Eight Indonesians of Tablighi Jamaat were tested positive in [[Karimnagar]] in Telangana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-in-india-high-alert-in-telangana-after-8-indonesians-test-positive-for-covid-19-1657355-2020-03-19|title=Coronavirus in India: High alert in Telangana after 8 Indonesians test positive for Covid-19|last=HyderabadMarch 19|first=Indo-Asian News Service|last2=March 19|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Ist|first3=2020 12:45}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/covid-19-telanganas-karimnagar-reports-eight-covid-19-positive-cases-city-under-lockdown-815287.html|title=COVID-19: Telangana's Karimnagar reports eight COVID-19 positive cases; city under lockdown|date=2020-03-19|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> They had arrived from Hazrat Nizammudin, Delhi on March 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://telanganatoday.com/karimnagar-six-secondary-contacts-of-indonesian-preacher-shifted-to-isolation-ward|title=Karimnagar: Six secondary contacts of Indonesian preacher shifted to isolation ward|last=AuthorTelanganaToday|website=Telangana Today|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> Security agencies had traced the link of these cases to Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/markaz-leadership-resisted-then-nsa-ajit-doval-dropped-by-at-2-am/story-RhL243HMbRgTGBbriNIVzL.html|title=Markaz leadership resisted, then NSA Ajit Doval dropped by at 2 am|date=2020-04-01|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n* On March 21, two Thai Nationals in Erode, Tamil Nadu were reported as positive case number 5 and 6. They had attended this congregation in Delhi in early March.<ref>{{Cite news|last=M|first=Serena Josephine|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/25-of-67-patients-directly-or-indirectly-linked-to-thai-nationals/article31212197.ece|title=25 of 67 patients directly or indirectly linked to Thai nationals|date=2020-03-30|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/tamil-nadu-reports-17-fresh-coronavirus-cases-tally-now-67-819262.html|title=Tamil Nadu reports 17 fresh coronavirus cases; tally now 67|date=2020-03-30|website=Deccan Herald|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref> \n*On March 26, Jammu and Kashmir reported first death to the pandemic, a 65 year old who had attended this congregation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/tracking-covid-19-super-spreader-from-j-k-to-tablighi-event-in-delhi-and-back-via-up/articleshow/74911674.cms?from=mdr|title=Tracking COVID-19 'super spreader': From J-K to Tablighi event in Delhi and back via UP|date=2020-03-31|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> At that time, more than 40 of 48 cases in the region was tracked back to this patient.<ref name=\":7\" />\n* On March 31, 57 new cases were reported in Tamil Nadu. 80 out of total 124 cases in the state are linked to Tablighi Jamaat cluster.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tamil-nadu-reports-57-new-covid-19-cases-in-one-day-79-attended-tablighi-jamaat-state-tally-at-124-1661904-2020-03-31|title=Tamil Nadu reports 57 new Covid-19 cases in one day, 79% attended Tablighi Jamaat. State tally at 124|last=ChennaiMarch 31|first=Shalini Lobo|last2=March 31|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Ist|first3=2020 21:56}}</ref> \n\n==== April ====\n\n* First positive case from [[Dharavi]] in [[Mumbai]] who eventually died on April 1, has hosted 10 Tablighi Jamaat members between March 22 and March 25.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/coronavirus-in-mumbai-dharavi-man-covid-19-patient-hosted-10-tablighi-jamaat-members-nizamuddin-604366|title=Coronavirus in Mumbai: Dharavi man who died due to COVID-19 hosted 10 Tablighi Jamaat members|last=Jaiswal|first=Priya|date=2020-04-04|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/coronavirus/news/dharavi-man-who-died-hosted-10-tablighi-jamaat-members/articleshow/74976875.cms|title=Dharavi man who died hosted 10 Tablighi Jamaat members|last=Marpakwar|first=Chaitanya|last2=Dalvi|first2=Vinay|website=Mumbai Mirror|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Marpakwar|first3=Lata MishraChaitanya|last4=Dalvi|first4=Vinay|last5=Mishra|first5=Lata|last6=Apr 4|first6=Mumbai Mirror {{!}} Updated:|last7=2020|last8=Ist|first8=08:31}}</ref>\n* On April 1 and 2  Tamil Nadu reported 110 and 74 positive cases respectively, all of them had related to this cluster.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tamil-nadu-new-coronavirus-cases-linked-nizamuddin-event-tabligh-1662243-2020-04-01|title=Tamil Nadu reports 110 new coronavirus cases, all linked to Nizamuddin event|last=ChennaiApril 1|first=Shalini Lobo|last2=April 1|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Ist|first3=2020 19:40}}</ref>\n* On April 3, 100 cases in Tamil Nadu and 42 in Uttar Pradesh are related to this cluster.<ref name=\":5\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://telanganatoday.com/44-new-positive-covid-19-cases-in-up-42-attended-nizamuddin-event|title=44 new positive COVID-19 cases in UP, 42 attended Nizamuddin event|last=AuthorANI|website=Telangana Today|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n*On April 4, in Tamil Nadu 73 people who had taken part in congregation are tested positive.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/coronavirus-tn-reports-74-new-cases-total-goes-up-to-485/article31258036.ece|title=Coronavirus {{!}} TN reports 74 new cases; total goes up to 485|date=2020-04-04|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-04|others=PTI|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> In Assam, 25 out of 26 cases reported until this date had taken part in this event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/assam-coronavirus-infected-man-met-111-search-for-silent-carrier-on-2206264|title=Assam Coronavirus-Infected Man Met 111, Search For \"Silent Carrier\" On|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n*On April 5, Tamil Nadu positive cases reached 571 in which 522 are related to this hotspot.<ref name=\":6\" /> In Uttar Pradesh, out of 139 out of 283 cases reported until this date has linkage to this cluster and in Delhi it is 320 out of 503 total cases.<ref name=\":8\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/delhi-new-covid19-cases-coronavirus-lockdown-604836|title=58 new COVID-19 cases reported in Delhi, tally rises to 503|last=Pathak|first=Analiza|date=2020-04-05|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n==Related casualties==\nIn [[Prayagraj]] in [[Uttar Pradesh]], a man was shot dead for making remarks against Tablighi Jamaat. \n<ref>\n[https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/up-man-shot-dead-at-tea-shop-for-blaming-tablighi-jamaat-for-coronavirus-spread-1663552-2020-04-05 UP man shot dead at tea shop for blaming Tablighi Jamaat for coronavirus spread], India Today, 5 April 2020.\n</ref>\n\nIn the Una district in [[Himachal Pradesh]], a man hanged himself due to taunts from fellow villagers for having come in contact with Tablighi Jamaat missionaries.<ref>\n[https://www.tribuneindia.com/news/himachal/himachal-man-commits-suicide-after-insults-over-coronavirus-spread-post-tablighi-congregation-65978 Taunted over coronavirus spread after Tablighi meet, Himachal man commits suicide], The Tribune (Chandigarh), 5 April 2020.\n</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in India]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|timestamp=20200402133413|year=2020|month=April|day=2|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Dellhi|date=2 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{use Indian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Current|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox event\n| image                    =\n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  =\n| time                     =\n| duration                 = \n| date                     = 1 March - 21 March (congregation) \n| venue                    =  [[Banglewali Mosque|Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] \n| location                 = [[Nizamuddin West]], [[Delhi]], India\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            = Nizamuddin Markaz hotspot\n| type                     = Religious congregation \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   =\n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             = atleast 9000 people \n| awards                   = \n| url                      = \n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    = \n}}\n\nA [[Tablighi Jamaat]] religious congregation that took place in Delhi's [[Banglewali Mosque|Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] in early March has emerged as a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] [[super-spreader]] event, after more than 900 confirmed cases<ref name=ndtv>{{cite news |title=647 COVID-19 Cases In Last 2 Days Linked To Islamic Sect Meet In Delhi |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/647-coronavirus-cases-found-in-last-two-days-linked-to-islamic-sect-gathering-in-delhi-says-governme-2205635 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=NDTV}}</ref> and at least 10 deaths linked to the event were reported across the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=India confronts its first coronavirus \u2018super-spreader\u2019 \u2014 a Muslim missionary group with more than 400 members infected |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/india-coronavirus-tablighi-jamaat-delhi/2020/04/02/abdc5af0-7386-11ea-ad9b-254ec99993bc_story.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Washington Post}}</ref> Over 9,000 missionaries may have attended the congregation, with the majority being from various states of India,<ref name=\"TOI 2 April\">\n{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: About 9,000 Tablighi Jamaat members, primary contacts quarantined in country, MHA says |newspaper=The Times of India |agency=PTI |date=2 April 2020 |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-about-9000-tablighi-jamaat-members-primary-contacts-quarantined-in-country-mha-says/articleshow/74948832.cms}}\n</ref><ref name=\"HT 2 April\">\n{{cite news |title=How Nizamuddin markaz became Covid-19 hotspot; more than 8,000 attendees identified |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=2 April 2020 |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/how-nizamuddin-markaz-became-a-hotspot-for-covid-19-8-000-people-identified/story-zedKlaDNTPpbDLdMsgExAM.html}}\n</ref> and 960 attendees from 40 foreign countries.<ref>\n{{cite news |title=379 Indonesians among foreigners from 40 countries attended Tablighi Jamaat gathering: Sources |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/379-indonesians-among-foreigners-from-40-countries-attended-tablighi-jamaat-gathering-sources20200403152720/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=ANI}}\n</ref> By 4 April, 1,023 cases in 17 states are linked to the Tablighi Jamaat hotspot, representing 30% of all confirmed cases in India.<ref name=\"PTI 4 April\"/> A total of 22,000 people including Tablighi Jamaat members and their contacts have been quarantined across the country.<ref name=\"quarantined 4 April\">\nPTI, [https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/nearly-22000-tablighi-jamaat-members-contacts-quarantined-across-country-mha-1663301-2020-04-04 Nearly 22,000 Tablighi Jamaat members, contacts quarantined across country: MHA], India Today, 4 April 2020.\n</ref>\n\nTablighi Jamaat has received widespread criticism from the Muslim community for holding the congregation despite a ban on public gatherings being issued by the [[Government of Delhi]] on 13 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat draws widespread condemnation from Muslim society |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/academics-among-muslims-condemn-the-act-of-tablighi-jamaat-in-nizamuddin/article31218658.ece |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Hindu Business Line}}</ref>\n\n==Event==\nThe congregation took place at the Nizamuddin Markaz Masjid in March and had more than 9,000 attendees from various parts of the world. Many of the attendees reportedly travelled across the country for missionary work<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/1400-nizamuddin-event-attendees-from-maha-traced-tope/articleshow/74965665.cms|title=1,400 Nizamuddin event attendees from Maha traced: Tope|date=2020-04-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> and were scheduled to conduct Chilla, a preaching activity, in different states throughout the year. The event carried on, despite the [[Government of Delhi]] issuing a ban on all public gatherings on March 13, with over 2,000 participants present at the mosque on that date. According to the Home Ministry, there were 1,746 people in the Markaz on 21 March.<ref name=insight>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat's defiance spreads concern {{!}} India Today Insight |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/web-exclusive/story/the-new-threat-from-tablighi-jamaat-1661938-2020-04-01 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, the Jamaat approached the Nizamuddin police station after six participants tested positive for coronavirus.<ref name=insight/> By the time, thousands of attendees had already travelled by five trains to other parts of the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=5 trains, thousands of passengers under scanner over travelling with Tablighi Jamaat participants |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/5-trains-thousands-of-passengers-under-scanner-over-travelling-with-tablighi-jamaat-participants/articleshow/74929663.cms |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Times of India}}</ref> On 26 March, the first death linked to the event was reported in [[Srinagar]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]], a 65-year-old man who had tested positive on 24 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kashmir's First Coronavirus Death Reveals Saga of Negligence and Confusion; Probe Underway |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/kashmirs-first-coronavirus-death-reveals-saga-of-negligence-and-confusion-probe-ordered-2553873.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=News18}}</ref> After a national lockdown went into effect on 25 March, more than 1,000 participants were stranded at the mosque, of whom as many as 300 showed symptoms of the virus. Local authorities began clearing the premises and cordoned off the Nizamuddin area.<ref name=\":7\">{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Search for hundreds of people after Delhi prayer meeting |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-52104753 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=BBC}}</ref>\n\n===Spread===\nA cluster spread became apparent in the following days as cases traced back to the event were reported in several states. In [[Telangana]], five people who attended the event died on 30 March. Dozens of people tested positive in other places such as [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] and [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]]. State governments scrambled to trace the whereabouts of the attendees.<ref>{{cite news |title=Delhi area under watch: Officials link 5 Telangana deaths to Nizamuddin mosque, trace 1,600 people |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/delhi/parts-of-delhis-nizamuddin-west-cordoned-off-after-covid-19-cases-traced-to-area-6338798/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nAs of 3 April, more than 950 confirmed cases were detected across 14 states and union territories in the country, including 97 percent of the total cases confirmed in the country on 2 and 3 April (647 out of 664 cases).<ref name=ndtv/><ref>{{cite news |title=647 coronavirus positive cases in two days linked to Tablighi Jamaat |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/647-coronavirus-positive-cases-in-two-days-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat/articleshow/74967407.cms |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Economic Times}}</ref> Tamil Nadu was the worst affected state, as 364 of the 411 people who tested positive had attended the event.<ref>{{cite news |title=102 new Covid-19 cases in Tamil Nadu; state's tally reaches 411 |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/102-new-covid-19-cases-in-tamil-nadu-state-s-tally-reaches-411-11585922977996.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Livemint}}</ref> 259 of the 386 cases in Delhi<ref>{{cite news |title=2 more deaths in Delhi, one a Tablighi Jamaat man; 93 new Coronavirus cases reported |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/2-more-covid-deaths-in-delhi-one-a-tablighi-jamaat-man-93-new-cases-reported/articleshow/74975751.cms |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Times of India}}</ref> and 140 of the 161 cases in Andhra Pradesh were linked to the event.<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19: AP reports first death; 140 of 161 cases linked to Markaz Nizamuddin |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/covid-19-ap-reports-first-death-140-of-161-cases-linked-to-markaz-nizamuddin-11585899097389.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Livemint}}</ref> All nine deaths reported in Telangana until 2 April were of people who had returned from the congregation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Three more Covid-19 deaths in Telangana, all linked to Markaz event |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/three-more-covid-19-deaths-in-telangana-all-linked-to-markaz-event/story-X0xlWmGltcOvrQClVdEzAI.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n\nThe Srinagar man who died on 26 March was identified as a [[super-spreader]] as he travelled by road, rail and air from Delhi to Srinagar via Uttar Pradesh, as officials feared that he may have spread it to several people along the way.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Delhi Police books Tablighi Jamaat head as Nizamuddin centre emerges as hotspot; 1,339 workers quarantined, says MHA |url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-delhi-police-books-tablighi-jamaat-head-as-nizamuddin-centre-emerges-as-hotspot-1339-workers-quarantined-says-mha-8211721.html |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Firstpost}}</ref> \n\n===Tracing of attendees===\nBy 2 April, Maharashtra, Telangana and Karnataka traced down 1,325, 1,064 and 800 attendees of the event respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat: 1,325 of 1,400 attendees traced in State |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/coronavirus-two-from-pune-district-who-went-to-nizamuddin-conclave-test-positive/article31234627.ece |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nine Delhi returnees die in Telangana, 21 new COVID-19 cases |url=https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/news/india/nine-delhi-returnees-die-in-telangana-21-new-covid-19-cases-reported-in-andhra-pradesh/articleshow/74946154.cms |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=Pune Mirror}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=1,500 from Karnataka attended Tablighi Jamaat |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/karnataka/2020/apr/02/15k-from-ktaka-attended-jamaat-2124607.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref> Tamil Nadu identified and quarantined 1,103 of the 1,500-odd participants from the state.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: How difficult was tracking the Jamaat event attendees from Tamil Nadu? |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/coronavirus-how-difficult-was-tracking-the-jamaat-event-attendees-from-tamil-nadu-820525.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=Deccan Herald}}</ref> 569 residents of Uttar Pradesh who attended the event were tracked down by the state police with the help of surveillance and local intelligence units.<ref>{{cite news |title=Police trace 569 residents of Uttar Pradesh who attended Tablighi Jamaat |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/lucknow/police-trace-569-residents-of-uttar-pradesh-who-attended-tablighi-jamaat/articleshow/74940549.cms |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=Times of India}}</ref> Andhra Pradesh reportedly detected around 800 of the 1,085 people of the state who attended the congregation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi attendees\u2019 motive under police scanner |url=https://www.sundayguardianlive.com/news/tablighi-attendees-motive-police-scanner |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The Sunday Guardian}}</ref> Gujarat Police identified 42 attendees from the state who attended the event.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/72-tabligh-attendees-traced-in-gujarat-one-dead-of-covid-19/article31228520.ece|title=Coronavirus {{!}} 72 Tabligh attendees traced in Gujarat; one dead of COVID-19|date=2020-04-01|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-05|others=Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 April, it was reported that the [[Delhi Police]] had found more than 500 foreign preachers \"hiding in 16-17 places\" in the city.<ref>{{cite news |title=Over 500 Foreigners Who Attended Tablighi Jamaat Found Hiding in Delhi Mosques |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/over-500-foreigners-who-attended-tablighi-jamaat-found-hiding-in-delhi-mosques-2563791.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=News18}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath and action==\nThe Union Home Ministry instructed state governments to track down the 824 foreign attendees of the congregation, asking them to screen, quarantine and deport such individuals.<ref>{{cite news |title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=The Hindu}}</ref> On 2 April, the Home Ministry identified 960 foreigners who took part in the event and blacklisted their visas for violation of [[The Foreigners Act, 1946]] and [[Disaster Management Act, 2005]], and asked the DGPs of respective states and union territories to initiate legal action against them.<ref>{{cite news |title=960 foreigners linked to Tablighi Jamaat blacklisted, visas cancelled by MHA |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/foreigners-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-blacklisted-visas-cancelled-by-mha-1662648-2020-04-02 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n\nDelhi government ordered an FIR against [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]], the head of Nizamuddin faction of the Tablighi Jamat.<ref name=\"standard\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-120033100007_1.html |website=business-standard |publisher=[[Business Standard]] |accessdate=30 March 2020 |date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatoday\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-1661514-2020-03-30 |website=India Today |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref> On 31 March 2020, FIR was filed against Kandhlawi and others by Delhi Police Crime Branch under Section 3 (penalty for offence) of the [[Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897]] and Sections 269 (Negligent act likely to spread infection of disease), 270 (malignant act likely to spread infection of disease), 271 (disobedience to quarantine rule) and 120b (punishment of criminal conspiracy) of the IPC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-in-india-tablighi-jamaat-preacher-others-booked-for-violating-govt-guidelines-on-religious-gatherings-1661870-2020-03-31|title=Coronavirus in India: Tablighi Jamaat preacher, others booked for violating govt guidelines on religious gatherings|first1=India Today Web Desk New|last1=DelhiMarch 31|first2=2020UPDATED:|last2=March 31|first3=2020 21:56|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref> After Kandhlawi and five associates named in the FIR went missing, Crime Branch began conducting raids on possible hideouts in Delhi and Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cops carry out raids to nab Tablighi head |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/apr/02/cops-carry-out-raids-to-nab-tablighi-head-2124565.html |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nDelhi Police launched an investigation into a leaked audio clip in which Kandhlawi allegedly asked his followers \"to not abide by government/medical guidelines with regards to the coronavirus outbreak.\" He was also heard saying, \"This is not the time when you leave your prayers or meeting people just because doctors are saying. When [[Allah]] has given this disease, then no doctor or medicine can save us.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=It\u2019s time to stay in mosques, Allah will save us: Tablighi Jamaat chief told followers in leaked audio |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/it-s-time-to-stay-in-mosques-allah-will-save-us-tablighi-jamaat-chief-told-followers-in-leaked-audio-1662297-2020-04-01 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref> A day later, Kandhlawi released an audio message on [[YouTube]] from his hiding, saying, \"I am in self-quarantine in Delhi as advised by the doctors and appeal to all Jamaat wherever they are in the country to follow the directives of the law.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Hiding Tablighi Jamaat chief releases audio message, says he is in self quarantine |url=https://scroll.in/latest/958015/coronavirus-hiding-tablighi-jamaat-chief-releases-audio-message-says-he-is-in-self-quarantine |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Scroll.in}}</ref>\n\nAccording to reports, around 160 attendees who were quarantined at a railway facility in Delhi \"misbehaved\" and \"spat on\" doctors and healthcare personnel who were attending to them. They also allegedly raised objection to the food served and roamed around the facility in violation of the norms of the isolation ward.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat attendees misbehave with staffers, spit at doctors at Delhi quarantine units |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-india-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-misbehave-staffers-spit-doctors-delhi-quarantine-units-1662322-2020-04-01 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref> Attendees quarantined at a facility in [[Ghaziabad]] reportedly roamed around naked in the facility and made lewd comments and directed vulgar signs at the nurses.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/tabligh-members-undergoing-treatment-not-cooperating-doctors-to-delhi-govt/articleshow/74969727.cms?from=mdr|title=Tabligh members undergoing treatment not cooperating: Doctors to Delhi govt|date=2020-04-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat patients making vulgar signs, roaming nude inside hospital: Ghaziabad CMO tells police |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tablighi-jamaat-patients-making-vulgar-signs-roaming-nude-inside-hospital-ghaziabad-cmo-tells-police-1662659-2020-04-02 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref> Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister [[Yogi Adityanath]] condemned the actions, called the patients \"enemies of humanity\" and invoked the [[National Security Act (India)|National Security Act]] against them.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ghaziabad/ghaziabad-tabligh-jamaat-members-misbehave-with-nurses-up-govt-to-invoke-nsa/articleshow/74967055.cms|title=Ghaziabad: Tablighi Jamaat members misbehave with nurses; UP govt to invoke NSA {{!}} Ghaziabad News - Times of India|last=Apr 3|first=PTI {{!}} Updated:|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-04|last3=Ist|first3=19:47}}</ref> In [[Bihar]], stones were pelted at police officers who had gone for tracking Tablighi Jamaat attendees.<ref>{{cite news |title=3 held in Bihar's Madhubani for pelting stones at cops tracking Tabligi Jamaat attendees |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/apr/01/3-held-in-bihars-madhubani-for-pelting-stones-at-cops-tracking-tabligi-jamaat-attendees-2124401.html |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nAdministration of TJ had said they are willing to dispatch hundreds of missionary to their respective nation & states but as the lockdown is in place they are helpless.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/nizamuddin-markaz-had-sought-help-from-authorities-for-vacating-premises/article31214305.ece|title=Nizamuddin markaz had sought help from authorities for vacating premises|first=Staff|last=Reporter|date=March 31, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>Press Release and relevant letters released by the Markaz</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://khabar.ndtv.com/news/india/coronavirus-total-case-in-india-nizamuddin-markaz-organiser-says-continuously-asking-curfew-pass-and-2203440|title=\u0915\u094c\u0928 \u0939\u0948 '\u0918\u094b\u0930 \u0905\u092a\u0930\u093e\u0927\u0940': \u0905\u0917\u0930 \u0924\u092c\u0932\u0940\u0917\u0940 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924 \u0928\u0947 \u092e\u093e\u0902\u0917\u093e \u0925\u093e 17 \u0917\u093e\u0921\u093c\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092b\u094d\u092f\u0942 \u092a\u093e\u0938, \u0924\u094b \u0915\u093f\u0938\u0928\u0947 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u0940 \u092c\u093e\u0924|website=NDTVIndia}}</ref>\n\n==Cases linked==\n\nAccording health authorities, until 2 April, among 2000 positive cases in India nearly 400 cases epidemiological linkage can be traced to the Tablighi Jamaat cluster.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://theprint.in/india/one-in-indias-five-covid-19-patients-is-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-and-its-delhi-event/393993/ |title=One in India\u2019s five Covid-19 patients is linked to Tablighi Jamaat and its Delhi event |last=Yadavar |first=Swagata |date=2020-04-02 |website=ThePrint |language=en-US |access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/400-covid-19-cases-with-linkage-to-tablighi-jamaat-found-health-ministry/articleshow/74951562.cms |title=400 COVID-19 cases with linkage to Tablighi Jamaat found: Health Ministry {{!}} India News - Times of India |last=Apr 2 |first=ANI {{!}} |last2=2020 |website=The Times of India |language=en |access-date=2020-04-03 |last3=Ist |first3=18:55}}</ref> By 3 April, 647 cases are reported which are related to this cluster.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/647-positive-cases-from-14-states-in-last-two-days-are-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-health-ministry/articleshow/74967407.cms |title=647 coronavirus positive cases from 14 states in last two days are linked to Tablighi Jamaat: Health Ministry |date=2020-04-03 |work=The Economic Times |access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> By 4 April, 1,023 cases with links to this cluster were reported which is about 30% of total cases in the country.<ref name=\"PTI 4 April\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/covid-19-positive-cases-links-tablighi-jamaat-reported-17-states-health-ministry-1663313-2020-04-04 |title=1,023 Covid-19 positive cases with links to Tablighi Jamaat reported from 17 states: Health ministry |agency=Press Trust of India |website=India Today |date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing are some of the positive cases from different states as reported in media.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! State or UT !! Positive Cases\n!Deaths!! Ref(s)\n|-\n|[[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]]|| 9\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|[[Andhra Pradesh|Andhra pradesh]]|| 140 \n|1||<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://english.jagran.com/india/coronavirus-outbreak-295-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-test-positive-for-covid19-960-foreign-attendees-blacklisted-by-mha-10010317|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Nizamuddin Markaz trail widens with sharp spike in cases in Telangana, Delhi and UP|date=2020-04-03|website=Jagran English|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Assam]]|| 25\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" /><ref